<HEAD>Elephant Tramples West German Tourist To Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West German tourist was trampled to
death by an elephant that she tried to play with during a hike in
northern Thailand, a police officer said today.
   The officer, who asked not to be named, said Helga Torbirt, 49,
was killed in the accident Friday in Chiang Dao, a town about 20
miles north of the major northern city of Chiang Mai near the
Burmese border.
   Her hometown was not available.
   He said she and her husband, Andrew, and other tourists had just
completed a journey by raft and were taking a break in Wang Pasak
village.
   Tourists in the group said they were sitting by a stream when
Mrs. Torbirt approached an elephant that was bathing there. The
animal panicked, rushed toward the woman, grabbed her with its
trunk and threw her to the ground and trampled her, the officer
said.
