<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     03-27 0465</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0477</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Hit South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Much of the South got showers and thunderstorms today and rain
also fell in the Pacific Northwest, while parts of Kansas were so
windy that residents were warned of blowing dust.
   The storms reached from south central Kansas across central
Oklahoma and northwest Texas; from western Arkansas across
northeast Texas and northwest Louisiana; from central Louisiana
into northwest Mississippi; and over south central Minnesota.
   Evening thunderstorms in Texas on Sunday produced golf ball-size
hail near Winters, as well as three-quarter inch diameter hail at
Dougherty and Matador.
   In Kansas, winds gusted to 48 mph at Fort Riley and to 55 mph at
Salina. Advisories were posted for blowing dust this morning.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 1 a.m. EST
included more than an inch at Fort Sill, Okla., and almost an inch
at Leesville, La.
   The high temperature for the nation Sunday was 91 at McAllen,
Texas.
   Today's forecast: showers and thunderstorms scattered from
southern and eastern Arizona across the southern Plains, the
Mississippi Valley and the upper Great Lakes; possible severe
thunderstorms from south central Texas and the western Gulf Coast
and across Oklahoma to southern Kansas; and fair to partly sunny
skies across much of the remainder of the nation, with gusty winds
across the northern high Plains and the lower Rio Grande Valley.
   High temperatures were to be in the upper 40s and 50s from the
northern Pacific Coast across much of the Plateau to the northern
and central Rockies; in the 50s from eastern Montana to northwest
Upper Michigan and across northern Maine; in the 70s and lower 80s
from the southern and central high Plains to the southern and
middle Atlantic Coast; and in the 70s in the Southwest deserts.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 22
degrees at Houlton, Maine, to 75 degrees at Fort Lauderdale and Key
West, Fla., Laredo, Texas, and McAllen, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 57 fair; Boston 37 fair; Buffalo 48 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 56 fair; Cincinnati 54 fair; Cleveland 53 fair;
Detroit 41 foggy; Miami 72 fair; New York 41 fair; Philadelphia 42
fair; Pittsburgh 50 fair; Portland, Maine, 29 partly cloudy;
Washington 47 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 36 foggy; Chicago 61 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
64 drizzle; Denver 49 cloudy; Des Moines 64 partly cloudy;
Indianapolis 54 partly cloudy; Kansas City 62 windy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 60 partly cloudy; Nashville 58 partly cloudy;
New Orleans 66 partly cloudy; St. Louis 63 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 45 cloudy; Anchorage 29 windy; Las Vegas 49
partly cloudy; Los Angeles 52 fair; Phoenix 50 fair; Salt Lake City
40 fair; San Diego 53 fair; San Francisco 51 partly cloudy; Seattle
42 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 cloudy; Toronto 36 partly cloudy.
