<HEAD>Firebomb Thrown At Bar's Lenin Mural</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homemade firebomb was thrown against a
mural depicting Soviet revolutionary leader Vladimir Lenin on the
outside wall of a downtown bar, firefighters said.
   In addition to Lenin, the mural includes the communist hammer
and sickle emblems _ and a happy face.
   The firebomb, a bottle containing about a quart of a flammable
liquid, did little damage Sunday night at the Eastern Bloc bar,
firefighters said. The bar was not open at the time.
   Fire officials said witnesses saw a man walking near the bar
moments before the firebomb was hurled against the side of the
building.
