<HEAD>Illinois Delegation Arrives for Trade Talks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A delegation of Illinois businessmen, politicians
and labor leaders headed by Gov. James R. Thompson arrived Monday
to open what officials say will be the first U.S. state trade
office in the Soviet Union.
   After landing in Moscow, the group left immediately for
Leningrad for meetings with officials.
