   A day before being led off to the Albany County Jail on witness
tampering and tax evasion charges, Profeta had delivered a rousing
Easter sermon to his Long Island congregation.
   State Supreme Court Judge Joseph Harris rejected a last-minute
plea from Profeta's lawyer to sentence the minister to community
service work instead of jail. The lawyer, Stephen Scaring, said he
would consider appealing the sentence, which included five years on
probation.
