``Praise the Lord'' in the courthouse halls.
   At the Easter service, Profeta christened three babies,
performed a marriage and received a standing ovation from
parishioners.
   On top of the normal Sunday contribution, Profeta asked
churchgoers for an extra Easter offering. Those contributing were
given a wooden cross and a checkbook cover inscribed: ``You shall
remember the Lord your god, for it is he who gives you power to get
wealth.''
