<FIRST>r f BC-AvondaleContract     03-27 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Avondale Contract,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Orleans Shipyard Gets $319 Million Navy Contract</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AVONDALE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Navy has awarded Avondale
Industries Inc. a $319 million contract to build three more T-AO
fleet oilers, the suburban New Orleans shipyard announced Monday.
   The announcement brought to 16 the number of contracts for the
oil-replenishment ships awarded to Avondale since 1982, with the
total value of the contracts amounting to $1.9 billion, said Albert
L. Bossier Jr., the company's chairman and chief executive officer.
   Only two of the T-AOs in the Navy program were built elsewhere,
the shipyard said in a statement.
   It said about 1,200 Avondale employees involved in the T-AO work
would be retained due to the new contracts.
